quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,43,"And if We should will, We could drown them; then no one responding to a cry would there be for them, nor would they be saved"
  36,44,"Except as a mercy from Us and provision for a time."
  36,45,"But when it is said to them, ",1:[Of sins or of life in this world and the Hereafter.],2:[The conclusion of this sentence is understood to be "...they ignored the warning."]
  37,28,"They will say, ",1:[i.e., from our position of strength, oppressing us.  Or from where we would have grasped the truth, preventing us.]
  37,29,"They [i.e., the oppressors] will say, "
  37,30,"And we had over you no authority, but you were a transgressing people."
  38,7,"We have not heard of this in the latest religion.{1} This is not but a fabrication.",1:[Referring to Christianity or possibly the pagan religion of the Quraysh.]
  38,8,"Has the message been revealed to him out of [all of] us?"
  38,9,"Or do they have the depositories of the mercy of your Lord, the Exalted in Might, the Bestower?{1}",1:[Refer to footnote of verse 3:8.]
